page.title: 01WEY VALLEY EAST OF WOKING
page.content: The area is approximately twently miles south-west of London bisected by the new London orbital motorway M25. There are two main residential areas, Byfleet and West Byfleet in the north of the block. The housing is mainly one or two storied owner occupied homes and probably of a higher standard than average in the London area. The mainline railway means that many people can commute to work in London, most others need to drive away to work. A small number of industrial premises are scattered through the area, some are found on part of the old Brooklands racing circuit on northern boundary.
